FONT INFORMATION

The Menaion typeface is supposed to used for working with text of Ustav-era manuscripts. It contains the full repertoire of necessary Cyrillic and Glagolitic glyphs as well as glyphs of Byzantine Ecphonetic notation of the kind used in Cyrillic or Glagolitic manuscripts.

PLEASE NOTE: Menaion Unicode is BETA-STAGE SOFTWARE. Certain characters included in the font are under consideration for inclusion into the Unicode standard (or have not yet been proposed for inclusion). Therefore, some codepoints may change as the process of Unicode standardization is still ongoing. You are advised to periodically monitor http://www.ponomar.net/ for changes.

The following files are distributed in this package:
	* MenaionUnicode.otf : OpenType-CFF font (PostScript outlines) with OpenType features; the internal font name is Menaion Unicode
	* MenaionUnicode.woff : Web Open Font Format font (TrueType outlines) with OpenType features; the internal font name is Menaion Unicode
				  This font is intended for embedding into webpages
	* MenaionUnicodeSIL.ttf : TrueType font (TrueType outlines) with OpenType and SIL Graphite features;
				   The internal font name is Menaion Unicode TT
	The difference in internal font names allows you to have both the OpenType and TrueType versions installed simultaneously

	* MenaionUnicode.pdf : The PDF documents demonstrates some features of the font, and lists the available features

Available characters, OpenType and SIL Graphite features:
	* See the MenaionUnicode.pdf file for documentation and examples

